21/06/2004
LISBON, Portugal -- Greece made it to the second round of the European Championship despite losing to Russia on Sunday (20 June). The Greeks got their berth for the next round thanks to a victory by Portugal. Its 1-0 win kicked Spain out of the tournament. As football fans gathered to celebrate across Greece, Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis congratulated the players and their coach. (AP, Reuters, AFP, Bloomberg - 20/06/04)
